The paper deals with optimization problems related to integer programming and scheduling, which are typically studied in computer science subfields such as data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational complexity (cs.CC), game theory (cs.GT), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper's focus on exact algorithms and its use of novel proximity theorems suggest that it is more likely to be classified under cs.DS and cs.DM, while its applications to scheduling and bin packing problems suggest a possible classification under cs.CC and cs.GT. The mention of optimization also suggests a possible classification under cs.LG.
